Package: ggbranding
Title: Add personal branding to ggplot2 charts using Font Awesome 7 icons
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Guillaume", "Noblet", , "gnoblet@zaclys.net", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Easily add personal branding elements like social media icons
    to ggplot2 charts.  Provides simple functions to add GitHub, GitLab,
    LinkedIn, Bluesky, and other brand icons to plot captions with
    minimal effort. Automatically downloads Font Awesome fonts from
    official sources if not already available.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.2.0)
Imports:
    checkmate,
    fs,
    ggplot2,
    ggtext,
    glue,
    httr2,
    purrr,
    rappdirs,
    showtext,
    stringr,
    sysfonts,
    utils
Suggests:
    jsonlite,
    roxytypes,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/Needs/documentation:roxytypes
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE, packages = "roxytypes")
